127a67a6-8145-4777-b78a-82761694ce2a.0864bef9-d569-4edc-8a70-58795ecbcdfe.description=Description\: ------------- Permet de sélectionner un Worker Group au hasard. Le flow récupère en dynamique la liste des Worker Group puis il en prend un au hasard. Il créé les variables GLOBALES "overrideJRAS" et "overrideNRAS" enleur affectant le nom du Worker Group déterminé. Inputs\: -------- N/A Inputs Examples\: -------------------- N/A Outputs\: ---------- ou.errorMsg \: Message d'erreur en cas de dysfonctionnement Revision\: ---------- 18-10-2017 \: Capgemini - FBI version initiale Configuration\: ---------------- N/A 127a67a6-8145-4777-b78a-82761694ce2a.1c9fad06-dd81-476c-94e1-5d8464e3d6b8.description=
This operation can be used to find the SA version in the form of 'sasXXX' (Similar to the entries in the Selection List 'SAS Version'). Output of this operations  could be mapped to the input parameter 'coreVersion' which is used in other SA Operations. For SA version 6.x, this operation is not supported. For other SA versions, if the output variable 'coreVersion' is reported with 'UNKNOWN', then user is recommended to manually find the SA version to use in other SA Operations.

Inputs\:
coreHost - IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service.
corePort - HTTP(S) port of SA Web Service. By default it is '443'.
coreProtocol - HTTP / HTTPS. By default it is 'HTTPS'.
coreUsername - Username of the SA.
corePassword - Password of SA user.

Outputs\:
status - Operation completion Status.
coreVersion - SA version.  It could be one of [sas10, sas101, sas102, sas105, UNKNOWN].

Responses\:
success - retrieved successfully
failure - failed to retrieve data

Il ajoute une ligne formatée de la manière suivante \: resultExecution¤¤¤¤¤ La nouvelle entrée est ajoutée à la variable globale "VF.reportInfos" (initialisée par le flow "Report.init"). Exemples \: resultExecution¤Exec script "SASC.COLLECT.UNX"¤Collect server information¤srv123¤SUCCESS¤ resultExecution¤Exec script "SASC.COLLECT.UNX"¤Collect server information¤srv123¤FAILURE¤Server cannot be reached Si les caractères de séparation ne sont pas indiqués, l'opération utilisera les valeurs par défaut. Checks to see if a path is an existing file or folder.

Inputs\:
source - The full path path to check. This can be either a local path such as c\:\test.txt, or a unc path such as \\testhost\test.txt. This path is relative to the Windows RAS host that the operation is running on.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for username.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path does not exist.
success - The operation succeeded.

Creates a directory

Inputs\:
